{
    "name": "Demonologist",
    "type": "npc",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Demonologist",
            "type": "section",
            "text": "Demonologists can pull a creature from the <a aonid=\"13\" game-obj=\"Planes\">Abyss</a> and bend it to their will... for a time.<br/><br/><b><u><a aonid=\"5\" game-obj=\"Skills\" general=\"true\">Recall Knowledge - Humanoid</a></u> (<u><a aonid=\"14\" game-obj=\"Skills\">Society</a></u>)</b>: DC 23",
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 231",
                        "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 231",
                        "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zq7"
                    },
                    "page": 231
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Mystics",
            "type": "section",
            "sections": [
                {
                    "name": "Dark Rituals",
                    "type": "section",
                    "text": "Most rituals have a simple gp cost and skills. But what if a desperate NPC is willing to offer something darker, such as lives, souls, or worse? Such a nefarious ritual uses a normal ritual as a baseline, but the DCs and proficiency requirements might be reduced or waived entirely, as might any gp cost.",
                    "sources": {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 228",
                            "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 228",
                            "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zq7"
                        },
                        "page": 228
                    },
                    "subtype": "sidebar",
                    "sidebar_type": "advice_and_rules",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Advice and Rules",
                    "image": "Sidebar_1_AdviceAndRules.png"
                },
                {
                    "name": "Forms Of Fortune-Telling",
                    "type": "section",
                    "text": "",
                    "sources": {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 228",
                            "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 228",
                            "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zq7"
                        },
                        "page": 228
                    },
                    "subtype": "sidebar",
                    "sidebar_type": "additional_lore",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Additional Lore",
                    "image": "Sidebar_2_AdditionalLore.png"
                },
                {
                    "name": "Anthomancy",
                    "type": "section",
                    "text": ": Flowers. <br/><b>Astrology</b>: The cosmic caravan. <br/><b>Demonomancy</b>: Asking demons. <br/><b>Harrowing</b>: Harrow card readings. <br/><b>Haruspicy</b>: Entrails. <br/><b>Ichthyomancy</b>: The next fish caught. <br/><b>Mazomancy</b>: A nursing babe. <br/><b>Oneiromancy</b>: Dreams. <br/><b>Tyromancy</b>: Coagulation of cheese.",
                    "sources": {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 228",
                            "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 228",
                            "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zq7"
                        },
                        "page": 228
                    }
                },
                {
                    "name": "Mystic Cadres",
                    "type": "section",
                    "text": "Golarion has several mystic groups. <b>The Church of Razmir</b> offers a plan of 31 steps to divinity. The <b>Esoteric Order of the Palatine Eye</b> seeks celestial truths said to be granted by an ancient angel. <b>Knights of the Aeon Star</b> search for secret lore. Followers of <b>Rivethun</b>, dwarven animism, reach out to spirits to gain knowledge and earn favors.",
                    "sources": {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 228",
                            "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 228",
                            "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zq7"
                        },
                        "page": 228
                    },
                    "subtype": "sidebar",
                    "sidebar_type": "additional_lore",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Additional Lore",
                    "image": "Sidebar_2_AdditionalLore.png"
                },
                {
                    "name": "Mystic Rituals",
                    "type": "section",
                    "text": "The following are rituals sometimes cast by mystic groups. Those from the <i>Bestiary</i> are available only to appropriate celestials and fiends within the organizations. <ul><li><a aonid=\"21\" game-obj=\"Rituals\">Abyssal pact</a></li><li><a aonid=\"22\" game-obj=\"Rituals\">angelic messenger</a></li><li><a aonid=\"5\" game-obj=\"Rituals\">call spirit</a></li><li><a aonid=\"6\" game-obj=\"Rituals\">commune</a></li><li><a aonid=\"23\" game-obj=\"Rituals\">Infernal pact</a></li><li><a aonid=\"15\" game-obj=\"Rituals\">legend lore</a></li><li><a aonid=\"16\" game-obj=\"Rituals\">planar ally</a></li><li><a aonid=\"17\" game-obj=\"Rituals\">planar binding</a></li></ul>",
                    "sources": {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 228",
                            "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 228",
                            "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zq7"
                        },
                        "page": 228
                    },
                    "subtype": "sidebar",
                    "sidebar_type": "advice_and_rules",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Advice and Rules",
                    "image": "Sidebar_1_AdviceAndRules.png"
                }
            ],
            "text": "Those initiated into the hidden truths and forbidden secrets of the world are forever transformed\u2014or so they claim. To the cynical, a mystic is nothing more than a charlatan or zealot. Others profess to sense an aura around such luminaries and treat them with reverence, lest they offend some harbinger of unspeakable doom.",
            "sources": {
                "type": "source",
                "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                "link": {
                    "type": "link",
                    "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 228",
                    "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 228",
                    "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zq7"
                },
                "page": 228
            }
        }
    ],
